'''Forgotten Evergreens''' is an anomalous level of the backrooms.
==Description==
{{Blurimage|file=THE TREES.jpg|caption=It's so dark...|align=center}}
'''Forgotten Evergreens''' manifests as an infinite, dense forest of coniferous trees. The appearance is remarkably mundane, resembling a typical forest at night, but the environment is entirely synthetic. The trees possess no biological life cycle; they are rigid and unchanging, feeling cold and motionless to the touch. The level is set during a perpetual night. There is no moon, with the sky just being a pitch black empty void. The only light is a very faint, sourceless ambient glow that barely manages to get through the treetops, so that most of the level remains in absolute darkness.

The atmosphere of '''Forgotten Evergreens''' is laden with a dense, synthetic pine fragrance, something like industrial cleaning chemicals of a very strong grade. Because of this, the level is considered a severe mental hazard zone. A lengthy stay leads to a psychological condition called "Data Erosion." While the explorers drift through the woods, their recollections of the world they left behind progressively "blur" and vanish. It begins with insignificant matters, e.g. the flavor of a favorite dish, and then it develops into forgetting one's very self through the loss of the name or face of a loved one.

The acoustic properties of the forest are very anomalous. Sound waves are immediately absorbed by the artificial needles, so the range of any noise is limited to less than three meters. This results in a very quiet atmosphere, which causes severe imbalance and deprivation of the senses. People who have been in the forest say that the only continuous sound is a faint ringing in their ears, which is believed to be a psychological effect of the silence.

The ground appears to be covered in dark green grass and a thick layer of brown pine needles, giving a soft appearance. However, beneath this organic-appearing surface lies a floor of polished, whitish-gray concrete. This confirms the level's status as a structural "basement" for the layers above it. The transition between the grass/needles and the concrete appears seamless, as if the turf is merely a thin rug over the foundation.

The climate is lifeless and chilly, almost always staying right under 0°C (32°F). Because of the absence of wind and light, the air is wet, dense, and still. This ever, present, deep cold makes the effects of loneliness and forgetfulness even more intense, thus it is very likely that any individual who comes into this place gradually suffers both physically and mentally.

Rarely, the dense tree line will break to reveal a circular clearing where a singular, massive whitish-gray pillar emerges from the ground. These pillars are believed to be the structural supports for Level 1. Touching a pillar provides a momentary "re-sync" for the wanderer, temporarily halting the Data Erosion.

==Entities==
There are no entities in '''Forgotten Evergreens'''.
==Entrances & Exits==
===Entrances===
Every entrance here is random.

===Exits===
There are no confirmed reliable entrances or exits to '''Forgotten Evergreens'''. Exiting purely relies on sheer luck.



